        When Your Spouse's Name Isn't on the Title: What Married Brisbane Sellers Need to Know
      </h1>
      <p style="font-size:1rem;color:rgba(240,236,228,0.6);line-height:1.8;max-width:54ch;">
        In Queensland, only the registered owner on the certificate of title has the legal power to sell. If you are married but only one name is on the title, that fact shapes consent, caveats, and family law exposure during a sale.
      </p>
    </div>
